I
J
A
I^m
J^n
m,n\in\mathbb{N}
I^m+J^n\neq R
\Rightarrow
\exists P
I^m+J^n\subseteq P
\Rightarrow
I^m\subseteq P
J^n\subseteq P
\Rightarrow
I\subseteq P
J\subseteq P
\Rightarrow
I+J\subseteq P
I,J \subset R
I + J = R
i \in I
j \in J
i + j = 1
1 = 1^{2k} = (i + j)^{2k} = \sum_{\iota =0}^{2k} {2k \choose \iota} i^\iota j^{2k - \iota}  \in I^{2k} +  \dots + J^{2k} \subset I^k + J^k
k
k = \max (n,m)
I^k \subset I^n
J^k \subset J^m
1 = (i+j)^{2k} \in I^k + J^k \subset I^n + J^m
